{
    "comments": [
        {
            "type": {
                "id": 205,
                "en": "Reason the facility does not meet the criteria for NPRI",
                "fr": "La raison pour laquelle cette installation ne rencontre pas les critères de déclaration de l'INRP"
            },
            "comment": "As per the Guide for Reporting to the National Pollutant Release Inventory 2022-2024, only filterable particulate matter is required to be reported.  In previous years, both filterable and condensable particulate matter were reported.  With the inclusion of condensable particulate matter, the limits for PM10 and PM2.5 reporting were met.  With the removal of the condensable particulate matter, and utilizing only an USEPA approved emission factor for filterable particulate matter only, reporting limits are no longer met and therefore, no reporting is required."
        }
    ],
